---
import Container from "../components/container.astro";
import Features from "../components/features.astro";
import Hero from "../components/hero.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="">
  <Container>
    <Hero />
    <Features />

    <section class="mt-24 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#1D1D1F] text-center mb-10">
        Frequently asked questions
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <details
          class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group"
          open>
          <summary
            class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            What is Aero?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Aero is the place to publish prototypes and run user tests on them, in one loop. You publish by drag-drop, Figma link, or AI agent via MCP. Then you run recorded task-based tests on the exact URL you just published. AI surfaces the insights.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            How does the AI agent integration work?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Aero provides an MCP server you add to Claude with one command. Once connected, your agent can publish a project to a live URL and create a user test, all without leaving the conversation. When test results are ready, the agent can pull the AI-generated insights and act on them.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            What kinds of prototypes can I host?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Static sites (HTML/CSS/JS), Figma prototype links, or any folder you can zip and drag-drop. If your agent builds it as a static bundle, Aero can host it.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            How do user tests work?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            You define tasks for testers to attempt on your hosted prototype. Testers join through a link, and Aero records their screen and microphone. Each session is transcribed. AI generates a summary of findings across sessions that you or your agent can read.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            Do I need to find my own testers?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            [Placeholder: tester recruitment details to be confirmed. You can bring your own testers via a shareable link. Recruited tester panel details coming soon.]
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-[#F9FAFB] rounded-lg border border-[rgba(0,0,0,0.06)] p-5 md:p-7 transition-all duration-300 group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-base text-[#1D1D1F] cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between select-none">
            How much does Aero cost?
            <span class="ml-4 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M8 10l4 4 4-4" stroke="#6B6F76" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[#6B6F76] text-sm leading-relaxed">
            [Placeholder: pricing details to be confirmed. Sign up free to get started. See the Pricing page for current plan details.]
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Container>
</Layout>
